    "body": "Tracking issue to collect requirements to help guide how to design improvements for `vim.lsp.config/enable`.\n\n- Ability to prevent attaching an LSP to a buffer.\n  - If there are no workspace folders\n  - Based on buffer name/path\n\n- Dynamically building the command line arguments passed to start the server\n    - some language servers use command line flags to pass in configuration files if they aren't super good at following the configuration options in the LSP spec\n    - cases where java is used to execute the language server there are a ton of flags for the jvm runtime that can be built dynamically to properly link libraries/configure memory requirements/etc.",
